other_tests.findings: The uterus measures 6 cm x 4 cm x 4 cm, with the endometrium measuring approximately 3 mm. No focal uterine lesion is identified. Both ovaries are normal in size, with appropriate vascular waveforms identified, without evidence for torsion. There is a trace amount of free fluid in the pelvic cul-de-sac, likely physiologic. Neither kidney demonstrates hydronephrosis.
